C Programming Environment Setup
Language Characteristic: C is a compiled (not interpreted) language, which gives it high execution speed. It serves as the architectural foundation for many modern programming languages.

Workspace Initialization: The tutorial uses Visual Studio Code. To start, open a folder in VS Code and create your primary file using the standard extension: main.c.

1. Compiler Installation (GCC)
Check Status: Run gcc --version in the terminal to see if a compiler is already installed.

Download MSYS2: If the terminal returns an error, go to msys2.org, download the installer, and follow the provided setup instructions.

Configure Environment Variables (Windows):

Navigate to the MSYS2 binary directory (typically C:\msys64\ucrt64\bin).

Verify gcc.exe is in this folder, then copy the folder's path.

Search Windows for Environment Variables, edit the system Path variable, add a new entry, and paste the copied path.

